00:01:14.390 --> 00:01:18.230
So there's a big resemblance.

00:01:18.230 --> 00:01:21.020
And here you can see
one of Shingo's works.

00:01:21.020 --> 00:01:23.040
Maybe you want to say
something about it.

00:01:23.040 --> 00:01:25.940
SHINGO FRANCIS: OK, so
there's the three of us

00:01:25.940 --> 00:01:30.380
here in this one picture,
Christian on the left.

00:01:30.380 --> 00:01:31.690
On the right is my father.

00:01:31.690 --> 00:01:34.909
It's Sam Francis.

00:01:34.909 --> 00:01:36.450
Just a little brief
thing about him--

00:01:36.450 --> 00:01:38.840
he's an abstract expressionist.

00:01:38.840 --> 00:01:43.660
He was in Paris
in the '50s, kind

00:01:43.660 --> 00:01:47.570
of part of what they called
the Informel School in Paris

00:01:47.570 --> 00:01:49.730
with artists like Tapies.

00:01:49.730 --> 00:01:54.260
And in Japan, I don't know if
some people know Hisao Domoto?

00:01:56.870 --> 00:02:00.440
So he was part of that group.

00:02:00.440 --> 00:02:02.600
And then at the same time
since he was American

00:02:02.600 --> 00:02:04.590
and he had connections
in New York,

00:02:04.590 --> 00:02:07.490
he was also friendly with
the abstract expressionists

00:02:07.490 --> 00:02:09.889
in New York in the '50s.

00:02:09.889 --> 00:02:16.070
And that's how he kind of got
his name as a, quote, unquote,

00:02:16.070 --> 00:02:18.230
abstract expressionist.

00:02:18.230 --> 00:02:20.180
So this is one of his
works in the '60s.

00:02:20.180 --> 00:02:22.370
And then this
round thing you see

00:02:22.370 --> 00:02:28.430
here is a large drawing that's
suspended from the ceiling.

00:02:28.430 --> 00:02:32.600
And it's a type of drawing
where you could walk into it.

00:02:32.600 --> 00:02:38.270
So it's an installation as
well, so you're enveloped

00:02:38.270 --> 00:02:41.510
by this painting, drawing.

00:02:41.510 --> 00:02:45.980
And there's a line,
as you can see,

00:02:45.980 --> 00:02:48.230
at the middle of the
drawing, and that line

00:02:48.230 --> 00:02:51.230
has reference to--

00:02:51.230 --> 00:02:55.370
it could be like the horizon
and about perception,

00:02:55.370 --> 00:02:59.780
about how things from a distance
look very thin and far away,

00:02:59.780 --> 00:03:02.930
and then as you get closer
it starts to expand.

00:03:02.930 --> 00:03:06.750
And then the circle
represents time.

00:03:06.750 --> 00:03:11.900
So we're kind of in
this cyclical time frame

00:03:11.900 --> 00:03:16.750
where we live 24 hours a
day, seven days a week,

00:03:16.750 --> 00:03:20.960
30 days a month, and then
years, and then seasons.

00:03:20.960 --> 00:03:24.562
So we're basically
kind of in this cycle.

00:03:24.562 --> 00:03:25.770
That's how we live our lives.

00:03:25.770 --> 00:03:27.402
So that's what that references.

00:03:27.402 --> 00:03:28.860
CHRISTIAN AWE: And
it's quite huge.

00:03:28.860 --> 00:03:30.200
It's 90 meters.

00:03:30.200 --> 00:03:34.580
And the whole show is pretty
much based on works on paper

00:03:34.580 --> 00:03:44.510
and about bringing, basically,
people together and having

00:03:44.510 --> 00:03:47.890
kind of a show or face
off with one another.

00:03:47.890 --> 00:03:51.320
And here's a beautiful
example of how you

00:03:51.320 --> 00:03:52.592
reacted to your father's work.

00:03:52.592 --> 00:03:54.800
SHINGO FRANCIS: Yeah, part
of the concept of the show

00:03:54.800 --> 00:03:59.200
was also for Christian
and myself to do--

00:03:59.200 --> 00:04:03.590
since my father's historical
and that's in their collection

00:04:03.590 --> 00:04:07.400
and we're two living
semi young now--

00:04:07.400 --> 00:04:08.605
we used to say young artist.

00:04:08.605 --> 00:04:11.970
Now we saw we're
midcareer artists--

00:04:11.970 --> 00:04:18.589
and so to have a response to
a painting in the collection.

00:04:18.589 --> 00:04:22.370
So I chose this large painting.

00:04:22.370 --> 00:04:26.930
Mine is on the left side and
my father's on the right side.

00:04:26.930 --> 00:04:31.260
And the one on the
right is from 1978.

00:04:31.260 --> 00:04:33.350
